		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">A Mathematician's Apology</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><i><b>A Mathematician's Apology</b></i> is a 1940 essay by British mathematician <a href="/wiki/G._H._Hardy" title="G. H. Hardy">G. H. Hardy</a>. It concerns the <a href="/wiki/Aesthetics" title="Aesthetics">aesthetics</a> of mathematics with some personal content, and gives the layman an insight into the mind of a working <a href="/wiki/Mathematician" title="Mathematician">mathematician</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
